rComments: She was amazing! Always clear with explanations, good on laying out philosophers' point of view in simple, understandable ways. The papers weren't too hard, and the time given to do them was absolutely enough. Participation exercise is simple and worth 5% of the grade. The exam questions were posted a month-ish before the actual date.
Very incisive lectures. Clear with her expectations and advice on assignments.
By far one of the best Philosophy prof I've had. Really interesting course and she's very clear and easy to follow

Dr. Piercy was a very good professor. She was bright and happy all the time. She kept me engaged in lecture and asked many Iclicker questions. I had never taken a philosophy course before and this was an amazing introduction. My only complaint is that she would often run out of time in her lectures, and kept us past time multiple times.

She gives a lot of little assignments that build off of one another, which makes doing well on the assignments easy because you already know how to improve the next time. All the readings are posted in PDFs online (which is nice for saving money). She posts really detailed slides (but always posts them late). Overall, she's passionate and fair.

Prof. Pierce makes it really easy to understand the course! Her lecture slides have all the required information that you need to know to understand it clearly. She's also very very sweet! Her sweetness makes the course more interesting! Thanks to prof Piercy I am more interested in philosophy and want to take it next year as well!

Prof. Piercy is very soft spoken. So don't even try to record the lecture it won't pick up, haha. Sometimes the concepts are difficult to understand but Piercy does her best to take the readings and simplify them for everyone. She's actually a sweetheart and seems kind of dorky but that's okay! Also go to lecture because the iclicker is needed!!!!
